<br>
Level 50 hammer style is also worthless. And currently even with the new armor tables it's widely still believed hammer is better weapon because the best styles are taunt styles and hammer taunt uses low endurance cost. They did a horribly job balancing the weapon specs by only changing the armor tables and not fixing styles.<br>
<br>
Misanthrope <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/24/02 6:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hmmm</span><hr size=1> Hmmm no, sword users don't use their taunt style, EVEN in situations were they want/need to taunt the mob (NO to hit bonus -&gt; you'd better use medium bonus assault and pray it is enough to get mob's attention than whiff your taunt).<br>
With a counterproductive taunt style and a poorly designed parry chain (supposed to be the forte of the sword spec - second style in the chain has no to hit bonus and first and third styles both have bleed effects), sword spec needs a lot of work. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=allusernamestaken@teamskald>allUsernamesTaken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/13/02 11:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I agree</span><hr size=1> Since axe spec 6 there isnt 1 single combo (with the possible exception of havoc and tyr's) that is worth the effort to increase its skill.<br>
Take skalds for example: I doubt ill ever get axe 50, my shouts use end (cries) which leaves only 2 viable styles, plague and evernight. I use evernight almost all the time and plague when im the only tank, or plague in RvR.<br>
21 - Valkyrie's Shield Block  &lt;-- HAH<br>
4 - Cleave Parry  &lt;-- laugh<br>
10 - Pillager None <br>
18 - Plunder # 10 <br>
25 - Raider # 10  &lt;-- biggest laugh<br>
There is not one single viable combo for me to use in RvR, evernight and arctic lol yea i always get chance to get round the back of ppl. Positional styles in RvR are impossible to pull off with the network culling when a person is kiting, except anytime styles. We have no anytime style above lvl 6! wtf.<br>
Sword and hammer are the same.<br>
<br>
Now lets take for example Slashing styles of Albion H0 hum:<br>
-----<br>
6 - Uppercut – Medium fatigue cost, medium bonus damage, small bonus to hit <br>
15 - Opal Slash – Medium fatigue cost, Use after a successful Uppercut, medium bonus damage, causes light bleeding, bonus to hit<br>
-----<br>
29 - Amethyst Slash – Medium fatigue cost, low/medium bonus damage, large bonus to hit <br>
50 – Diamond Slash – High fatigue cost, use after successful Amethyst, High bonus damage, Very high bonus to hit <br>
-----<br>
I put 2 types and levels of styles in. First uppercut and opal slash, as a low lvl merc i used this ALL the time and remember HUGE dmg and good to hit. With medium endurance loss. Next is the big one Amethyst and diamond. Imo one of if not the best combos in the game. say no more.<br>
<br>
Being the melee realm i always wondered why we have the worst melee styles? Also although i profess to be no expert on nordic mythology i do not remember the Vikings to be &quot;just hold on chappie i want to get behind you&quot; they were run down a hill and swing sorta guys.<br>
<br>
I agree with the albion styles Camelot were (in theory) knights with codes of honour training everyday with techniques etc.. so its right imo that they were specialised and effecient with their blows. You could argue that the vinkings were less trained, less specialised fighters, this is true but they werent 'less effective'. They were brutal... yada yada<br>
<br>
In terms of game ballance mythic leaves a LOT to be desired with these styles. Im more than annoyed that they couldnt ballance a set of empty scales. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.showPrevMessage?topicID=35.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.showNextMessage?topicID=35.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.emailToFriend?topicID=35.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.threadControl?topicID=35.topic><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/closethread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=35.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=35.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub36.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum 